                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250113-126-victim669 t18250113-126-viclabel665"></join> -she is a widow, and lives in <placeName id="t18250113-126-crimeloc666">Grace's-alley, Wellclose-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250113-126-crimeloc666" type="placeName" value="Grace's-alley, Wellclose-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250113-126-crimeloc666" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250113-126-off662 t18250113-126-crimeloc666"></join>. On the 8th of December, between seven and eight o'clock in the evening, I missed this dowlas, which had been on a chair in the shop, about a yard from the door; I had seen it about three or four minutes before it was taken: I came to the door a minute or two after, and missed it. I looked out at the door, and saw the prisoner going down the alley; I pursued, and stopped him with it - I brought him back, and he asked me to have mercy upon him, as he had not had anything to eat for a day or two.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250113-126-person671">
                  WILLIAM 
                  DICKINSON
